  <h1>Utilities</h1>

  <h2>IE only</h2>

  <p>Applies CSS to specific IE versions. This only works for IE9 and IE 10.
      For IE9 the following must be at the top of your HTML</p>

  <p><code>&lt;!--[if IE 9]&gt;&lt;html class="ie9"&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;
  &lt;!--[if gt IE 9]&gt;&lt;!--&gt; &lt;html&gt; &lt;!--&lt;![endif]--&gt;
  </code></p>

  <h3>Usage</h3>

  <p><code>@include ie-only(9) {
      display: table-cell;
  }

  </code></p>

  <p><code>@include ie-only(10) {
      display: none;
  }
  </code></p>

  <h2>Scrollbar</h2>

  <h3>Scrollbars</h3>

  <p>Sets the scrollbar display value, possible values:</p>
  <p><code>none
  auto
  scroll
  </code></p>

  <p> Example: </p>
  <p><code>@include scrollbars(none);
  </code>
  </p>

  <h3>Momentum scrolling</h3>

  <p>Adds webkit momentum scrolling to an HTML element.</p>

  <p><code>.panel {
      @include momentum-scrolling;
  }
  </code></p>

  <h2>Spacings</h2>

  <p>Spacing variables allow for consistency across your application.</p>

  <p><code>$spacing-default: 16px;
  $spacing-small: $spacing-default / 2;
  $spacing-medium: $spacing-default * 2;
  </code></p>

  <h2>Measurements</h2>

  <h3>rem mixin</h3>

  <p>Allows you to calculate rems based on the base font size.
      You can pass in a property and number of values.</p>

  <p><code>@include rem(margin, 2px 4px 6px 8px);
  @include rem(font-size, 18px);
  </code></p>

  <h4>Calculate rem function</h4>

  <p><code>font-size: calculateRem(2px);
  </code></p>

  <h4>Calculate em function</h4>

  <p><code>font-size: calculateEm(2px);
  </code></p>

  <h2>-webkit-sibling-fix</h2>

  <p>Webkit on IOS 7 / 8 does not re-paint when sibling selectors are used. This is a fix to force
      redrawing.</p>

  <p>Put this on the element that is being updated.</p>

  <p><code>@include -webkit-sibling-fix;
  </code></p>
</div>